es, Parquet would likely be the preferred option due to its\ncolumnar nature and advanced compression. For initial loading into Snowflake, however, CSV often comes out\non top, especially for simpler datasets where the initial parsing speed becomes a significant factor.\nAuthoritative Links:\nSnowflake Documentation on Loading Data: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/sql/copy-intotable.html (Focus on the considerations for different file formats.)\nSnowflake Best Practices for Data Loading: https://community.snowflake.com/s/article/Best-Practices-forLoading-Data\nFile Format Support in Snowflake https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/data-load-considerationsformats.html"
