                "explanation": "The correct answer, A (BUILD_SCOPED_FILE_URL) and D (GET_PRESIGNED_URL), are non-deterministic file\nfunctions in Snowflake because their output can vary even when given the same input. Non-deterministic\nfunctions, in general, rely on external factors or time-sensitive data, making their results unpredictable for\nidentical inputs. BUILD_SCOPED_FILE_URL generates a URL that includes a temporary token for accessing a\nfile in a stage. The token's validity is time-bound, and therefore, a new URL generated at a later time, for the\nsame file, will be different due to the changed token. This reliance on a time-sensitive element renders it nondeterministic. Similarly, GET_PRESIGNED_URL creates a URL that grants temporary access to a file in a\nstage, including security credentials within the URL itself. These credentials have an expiration time.\nConsequently, successive calls with identical inputs will generate different URLs because the embedded\ncredentials and their associated expiration will change, making it non-deterministic. Conversely,\nBUILD_STAGE_FILE_URL (B), GET_ABSOLUTE_PATH (C), and GET_RELATIVE_PATH (E) provide predictable\noutputs based solely on their inputs, thus considered deterministic. They derive static path information based\non the stage or specified file locations and do not incorporate time-based or external elements. These\nfunctions consistently return the same values for equivalent inputs, making them reliable for deterministic\nprocesses. Understanding the distinction between deterministic and non-deterministic functions is crucial for\nefficient data pipeline management and maintaining data integrity in cloud data warehouses like Snowflake.\nHere are links for further research:\nSnowflake Documentation on File Functions: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/functions-file\n(Specifically, check the details on each file function mentioned.)\nSnowflake Documentation on Deterministic Functions: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/udfsgeneral#deterministic-and-non-deterministic-functions\nCloud Computing Concepts on Temporary Access URLs: Search for explanations of temporary signed URLs\nin cloud object storage, like AWS S3, Azure Blob Storage, or Google Cloud Storage, as Snowflake uses similar\nprinciples. (Example search: \"presigned url aws s3\")"
