e’s efficiency.\nOption B (Remove all dates and timestamps) is NOT a best practice: Dates and timestamps are crucial data\npoints in virtually any database system and are needed for time-series analysis and data interpretation.Removing them would render the data practically useless. Snowflake offers strong support for these\ndatatypes.\nOption E (Remove semi-structured data types) is NOT a best practice: Snowflake's strength lies in its ability\nto handle semi-structured data (like JSON, Avro, Parquet). Removing this data type limits Snowflake's\ncapabilities and leads to the loss of important information.\nTherefore, the two best practices when loading data into Snowflake are to load larger files (100-250 MB or\ngreater) and to avoid embedded characters in numeric data. This ensures data loading efficiency and correct\ndata interpretations."
