ive.\nManaged access schemas are useful, but they shouldn't be the only approach, and aren't directly related to\nACCOUNTADMIN object ownership.\nIn summary, Snowflake recommends balancing centralized management (via SYSADMIN) with granular\ncontrol through custom roles to minimize risk and improve operational efficiency when handling object\nownership. Custom roles assigned to SYSADMIN enforce the principle of least privilege, a cornerstone of\nrobust cloud security.\nAuthoritative Links:\nSnowflake Documentation on Access Control: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/security-accesscontrol-overview.html\nSnowflake Documentation on Roles: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/security-access-controlconfigure.html#configuring-access-control"
