                "explanation": "Reader accounts in Snowflake are special types of accounts created for sharing data\nwith users who do not have a regular Snowflake account. The ability to manage these\naccounts is restricted to specific roles with elevated privileges. The correct answer, A\nand E, indicates that only users with the ACCOUNTADMIN role and those with the\nCREATE ACCOUNT privilege can create and manage reader accounts.\nThe ACCOUNTADMIN role, being the most powerful role in Snowflake, has full control\nover the entire account, including the ability to create and manage other accounts suchas reader accounts. This is a fundamental concept in Snowflake's role-based access\ncontrol (RBAC) model, where roles like ACCOUNTADMIN inherit all privileges and\noperate at the highest level of the hierarchy. Users with the SECURITYADMIN role, while\nmanaging security, do not have the privilege to create accounts. The SYSADMIN role is\nfocused on system administration tasks within an account, not cross-account\nmanagement. The ORGADMIN role, also high-level, manages the entire Snowflake\norganization but does not directly manage reader accounts.\nThe CREATE ACCOUNT privilege is specifically designed to allow a user, even without\nthe ACCOUNTADMIN role, to create new accounts, including reader accounts, within the\norganization. This privilege enables a granular assignment of account creation\ncapabilities. By granting this specific privilege, access can be delegated without giving\nfull administrative control.\nTherefore, either a user with the all-encompassing ACCOUNTADMIN role or a user\nspecifically granted the CREATE ACCOUNT privilege can create and manage reader\naccounts. This control over account creation and management ensures that Snowflake\naccounts remain secure and that access is managed in a controlled and auditable\nmanner.\nFurther research can be done on Snowflake's official documentation regarding roles and\nprivileges:\nSnowflake Role-Based Access Control: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/userguide/security-access-control-overview.html\nSnowflake CREATE ACCOUNT Privilege: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sqlreference/sql/create-account.html\nSnowflake Reader Accounts: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/data-sharingreader-accounts.html"
