                  "C": "CREATE MASKING POLICY",
                  "D": "SET MASKING POLICY"
                },
                "answer": [
                  "B"
                ],
                "explanation": "The correct command to implement a pre-existing masking policy in Snowflake is ALTER TABLE\nor ALTER VIEW combined with the SET MASKING POLICY clause. While the option APPLY\nMASKING POLICY may seem intuitive, it doesn't exist as a standalone command in Snowflake's\nSQL syntax. CREATE MASKING POLICY is used to define a new masking policy, not to apply an\nexisting one. Therefore, option B is incorrect and should not be confused with the method used to\nimplement an already created policy. SET MASKING POLICY itself isn't a standalone command;\nit's a clause used within the context of altering tables or views.\nHere's the breakdown: Snowflake's masking policies are defined objects, separate from the data\nthey affect. Once created, these policies must be associated with specific columns of tables or\nviews. This association is achieved using the ALTER TABLE or ALTER VIEW statement, and the\nSET MASKING POLICY clause specifies which policy is to be applied to which column. This means,\nyou are altering the structure of an existing database object to incorporate the policy defined\nelsewhere. The masking policy will be active only when this alteration process has taken place.\nThis approach ensures a clear separation of concerns, allowing for reusable policy definitions\nacross multiple database objects.\nTo illustrate, a typical command might look like this: ALTER TABLE your_table MODIFY COLUMN\nyour_column SET MASKING POLICY your_masking_policy;. Therefore, the process involves first\ncreating a policy (using CREATE MASKING POLICY), then applying that policy to a column in a\ntable or view using ALTER TABLE or ALTER VIEW. There isn’t a single APPLY MASKING POLICY\ncommand.\nFurther research can be conducted via the official Snowflake documentation:\nALTER TABLE: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/sql/alter-table.html\nALTER VIEW: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/sql/alter-view.html\nMasking Policy: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/sql/create-masking-policy.html"
