                "explanation": "Here's a detailed justification for why options D and E are the correct choices regarding\ncolumn-level security in Snowflake:\nColumn-level security in Snowflake, a core component of its data governance\nframework, focuses on granular access control and data masking. Option D is correct\nbecause it precisely describes the mechanism: it allows administrators to grant user\nroles or specific users permission to access certain columns within a table while\nrestricting access to other columns within the same table. This is crucial for enforcing\nthe principle of least privilege, granting users access only to the information they need\nfor their role, thus minimizing the risk of accidental or malicious data exposure. Option E\nhighlights the masking policy functionality, which works in tandem with access control.\nMasking policies enable sensitive data to be hidden or obfuscated. Different policies\nsuch as NULL values, tokenization, or other transformations can be applied to data within\nspecific columns based on the user accessing that data. This capability ensures that\nusers with limited access will view only masked data, thereby preventing unauthorized\naccess to sensitive information. While column-level security strengthens data security,\nit does not directly optimize query performance (A) nor does it handle full database\nencryption (B) which is handled at storage level, nor restrict access to solely the tableowner (C), as access can be granted to other users through roles and privileges. In\nconclusion, column-level security is a critical element in Snowflake's approach to\nprotecting sensitive data, working by limiting access to specific columns and allowing\nthe masking of data values.\nFurther Research Links:\n1. Snowflake Documentation on Column-Level Security:\nhttps://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/security-column-level\n2. Snowflake Documentation on Data Masking:\nhttps://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/security-data-masking\n3. Snowflake Documentation on Access Control:\nhttps://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/security-access-control-overview"
