d to the data import process from Data Exchange.\nE. USAGE: The USAGE privilege is necessary to access objects within a database, such as tables\nor views. While needed after a database is created from a share, it is not the initial privilege to\nconsume the shared data from the data exchange itself.\nIn summary, a consumer needs the ability to create a database pointing to the shared data\n(CREATE DATABASE) and the permission to actually access that shared data (IMPORT SHARE).\nThese are the fundamental privileges needed to start working with data accessed via the\nSnowflake Data Exchange.\nAuthoritative Links:\nSnowflake Documentation on Data Sharing: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/datasharing-intro.html\nSnowflake Documentation on CREATE DATABASE: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sqlreference/sql/create-database.html\nSnowflake Documentation on IMPORT SHARE: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sqlreference/sql/grant-privilege.html"
