pplication while the cloud provider protects the physical\ninfrastructure.\nTherefore, the Cloud Services layer is principally concerned with managing metadata and optimizing queries,\nmaking options A and E the correct answers. The compute and storage aspects are handled by other\ndedicated layers in the Snowflake architecture.\nFurther Research:\nSnowflake Architecture: https://www.snowflake.com/blog/snowflake-architecture-overview/\nSnowflake Documentation on Cloud Services: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/intro-keyconcepts.html (Search for \"Cloud Services Layer\" on the page)"
