tats, so even this case is highly unlikely. The other options (COPY, SUM, UPDATE)\nalways require a warehouse. Because this question asks for examples, picking those which definitively will\nalways need a warehouse is a better approach. This is a rare, edge case. Therefore, A is incorrect in most\nrealistic scenarios and especially when the context is \"no queries have been executed previously\".\nIn summary, COPY, SUM, and UPDATE operations unequivocally necessitate a virtual warehouse to provide\nthe compute resources needed for data loading, aggregation, and modification, respectively. Option A is less\nconclusive.\nAuthoritative Links:\nSnowflake Virtual Warehouses: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/warehouses\nSnowflake COPY command: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/sql/copy-into-table"
