ance, it doesn't inherently address\nconcurrency, the ability to handle many concurrent queries.\nE. The use of warehouse indexing: Snowflake does not expose indexing to the user. Snowflake uses its\ninternal columnar storage for optimization of queries.\nIn summary, auto-scaling enables dynamic adjustment of compute resources, while multi-clustered\nwarehouses facilitate parallel processing, making them both essential features for handling high concurrency\nworkloads in Snowflake.\nAuthoritative Links:\nSnowflake Multi-Cluster Warehouses: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/warehouses-multicluster\nSnowflake Auto-Scaling: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/warehouses-considerations"
