lear the queued queries: This is a short-sighted solution. While it might\ntemporarily alleviate the issue by clearing the queue, the problem will quickly resurface if the warehouse is\nstill overloaded. It doesn't address the underlying capacity constraints.\nE. Limit user access to the warehouse so fewer queries are run against it: This is an undesirable and often\nimpractical solution. It restricts access to data and functionality, which negatively impacts business\noperations. The goal should be to provide adequate resources to handle the workload, not to limit access. A\nbetter strategy involves optimizing queries and scaling resources."
