t add memory for one specific query and rather distributes the query\nload across multiple clusters. Concurrency scaling is described in detail in Snowflake's\ndocumentation. Therefore, increasing warehouse size and processing data in batches are the most\neffective strategies to combat performance degradation caused by data spilling in Snowflake."
