e\navailability and access across different regions or clouds.\nCloud-agnostic Platform: Snowflake is designed to be cloud-agnostic and operate\nacross various cloud providers (AWS, Azure, GCP).\nData Sharing: Snowflake provides robust mechanisms for secure data sharing between\ndifferent Snowflake accounts.\nAuthoritative Links:\nSnowflake Documentation on Private Listings: Search the Snowflake documentation\nusing keywords like \"private listings,\" \"data sharing,\" and \"cross-cloud data sharing\".\nSpecifically look for the section explaining data sharing mechanisms and automated\ncross-cloud replication features\nSnowflake Marketplace: Explore the Snowflake Marketplace documentation to\nunderstand the differences between public, private, and personalized listings.\nGeneral Cloud Computing Concepts on Data Replication: Refer to resources on cloud\ncomputing principles, data management best practices, or specific cloud provider\ndocumentation."
