e Documentation on Virtual Warehouse Sizing:\nhttps://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/warehouses-sizing (This provides general\ninformation about warehouse sizes and resource allocation, indirectly highlighting how\nresource limitations affect concurrent query processing)\n2. Snowflake Documentation on Understanding Resource Consumption:\nhttps://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/cost-understanding (This helps understand\nthat concurrency often leads to increased, not decreased, credit consumption.)\n3. Blog on Query performance with concurrency in Snowflake:\nhttps://medium.com/@shailesh.mandal/concurrency-consideration-for-snowflakevirtual-warehouse-d13e5079864 (This external resource elaborates on the topic of\nconcurrency and its impact on query performance in Snowflake)\nIn summary, while Snowflake is built for concurrency, increasing the number of users will\ninevitably lead to performance degradation for demanding workloads as resource contention\nincreases."
