by itself. Snowflake monitors credits used but the\nQuery Profile shows you how your credits were spent by the query, not whether it\nexceeded a threshold you set separately. Therefore, the correct answers, B and D,\nshowcase issues where the Query Profile's execution breakdown provides a direct\ninsight to performance optimization.\nAuthoritative links for further research:\nSnowflake Query Profile Documentation: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/uiquery-profile.html\nSnowflake Join Optimization: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sqlreference/constructs/join-optimization.html\nSnowflake Data Pruning: https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/tables-clusteringkeys.html#benefits-of-clustering-and-pruning"
